  "prompt": "What should be my 12th board percentage to get admission in St. Xavier's College Autonomous, Mumbai for B.Com?",
  "response": "St. Xavier's College, Mumbai, is a prestigious institution, and admission can be quite competitive. For the Bachelor of Commerce (B.Com) program, admissions are typically based on merit, specifically your 12th-grade board examination scores. While the exact cut-off percentage can vary each year depending on factors like the number of applicants and their performance, it's generally advisable to aim for a high percentage to increase your chances.\n\nIn recent years, the cut-off percentage for B.Com at St. Xavier's has often been around 85-90% or higher. However, this can change annually, so it's important to check the college's official admissions guidelines and notifications for the most accurate and current information. Additionally, different quotas like in-house, minority, or open category can have varying cut-off percentages.\n\nTo ensure the best chance of admission, you should aim to score as high as possible in your 12th board exams and stay updated with any announcements from the college regarding admissions.",
